## DATABASE SCHEMA

Design a multi-tenant PostgreSQL schema with the following core tables:

organizations
- id, name, gstin (15-char validated), pan, address (JSON: line1, city, state, pincode), business_type (ENUM: b2b, b2c, mixed), plan_tier (ENUM: starter, growth, pro), plan_status, created_at

users
- id, org_id (FK), email, name, role (ENUM: owner, accountant, staff), clerk_user_id

invoices
- id, org_id, invoice_number (auto-generated per org: FY-sequential), invoice_date, due_date
- customer_id (FK), place_of_supply (state code)
- subtotal, cgst_amount, sgst_amount, igst_amount, total_amount, currency (default INR)
- status (ENUM: draft, sent, paid, cancelled, irn_generated)
- irn (e-Invoice Registration Number), ack_number, ack_date, qr_code_data
- upi_payment_link, payment_collected_at
- pdf_url, json_payload (JSONB — full GST invoice JSON)
- is_reverse_charge, is_export

invoice_items
- id, invoice_id, description, hsn_sac_code, quantity, unit, unit_price
- discount_percent, taxable_value
- gst_rate (ENUM: 0, 5, 12, 18, 28), cgst_rate, sgst_rate, igst_rate
- cgst_amount, sgst_amount, igst_amount, total

customers
- id, org_id, name, gstin (optional), pan, email, phone
- billing_address (JSON), shipping_address (JSON), place_of_supply
- customer_type (ENUM: registered, unregistered, consumer, export)

gst_returns
- id, org_id, return_type (ENUM: gstr1, gstr3b, gstr2a)
- period (YYYY-MM), status (ENUM: draft, submitted, filed, error)
- filed_at, arn (Acknowledgement Reference Number)
- json_payload (JSONB), error_log (JSONB)
- gstn_reference_id

