## CODE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS

- All monetary values stored as integers in paise (1 INR = 100 paise) — never floats
- All GST amounts rounded using ROUND HALF UP (as per GST rules)
- Full TypeScript strict mode — no `any`
- Every GSTN API call wrapped in retry logic with exponential backoff
- Every filing action must be idempotent (safe to retry)
- Audit log every invoice state change and GST filing action
- Write unit tests for: GSTIN validator, HSN lookup, GST calculator, GSTR-1 JSON builder
- Use Zod for all input validation on API routes
- Row-level security on Supabase or explicit org_id checks on every Prisma query

